name: Flying Canada's First NEO! Air Transat A321LR Calgary to Montreal
description:
Air Transat is Canada's third largest airline, and also the only operator of any Airbus A320neo family aircraft in the entire country!

That alone makes them stand out a fair bit, since Air Canada, WestJet, and Sunwing, all went with Boeing for their single-aisle replacements.

After 4 months without flying, it was great to see Air Transat back in the skies, and I wanted to see what it was like flying with them now, on board their very first A321neo!

*With thanks to @JonathanWinton123 for the Wizz Air cameo!
